-- We need a bijection ‚Ąē √ó ‚Ąē ‚ČÖ ‚Ąē for countable closure properties.
-- We'll use a simple diagonal enumeration.

-- Cantor pairing function: ‚ü®m, n‚ü© = (m + n)(m + n + 1)/2 + n
-- For simplicity, we postulate the basic pairing properties

private
